(Shutterstock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Kinshasa - The government of the Democratic Republic of Congo says more than 20 people have died in a collapse at a bush mine in the region of Masisi in North Kivu province. That's in the far eastern part of the country.The statement sent to reporters late on Friday and signed by government spokesperson Lambert Mende says the mine near the village of Rubaye collapsed on Friday evening. The statement says a search is on for any possible survivors.North Kivu is rich in minerals, including coltan and gold. Illegal and unregulated bush mines dot the countryside.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.